# UI Review Checklist

Before finalizing UI work, verify:

- Token usage: no hardcoded colors in feature styles.
- Semantics: action/info/success/warning/danger meanings are consistent.
- Typography: Roboto with deliberate weight usage.
- Motion: hover/pressed/focus behavior follows approved patterns.
- Accessibility: contrast, focus-visible, and reduced-motion behavior are present.
- Visual consistency: spacing, border radius, and depth match the design baseline.
- Dialog dismiss: every headered `<dialog>` uses `DialogCloseButton` (icon-only X, circular hover); confirmation dialogs use text buttons instead.

If any item fails, revise before marking the task complete.
